Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.35,0:00:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, as such,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.10,0:00:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,under the aristocratic republic system,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.23,0:00:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the aristocracy occupy all\Nof the important offices,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.27,0:00:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and at the time in Rome,\Nthe aristocrats, called the patricii,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.90,0:00:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the common people, called the plebs,\Nas well as minor farmers,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is boring. were clearly\Ndivided into two separate classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.87,0:00:25.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the two consuls, the dictator,\Nand the 300 senators
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.42,0:00:28.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were all selected from the aristocracy;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.13,0:00:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the senate was the highest\Nlegislative and advisory body,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the senators served for...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.59,0:00:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's all this commotion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.88,0:00:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Class A? Omichi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}?\NWhat are you all even doing here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.47,0:00:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hmm, probably.\NIf you're not here to learn, then leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.85,0:00:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you have\Nany desire to learn!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.93,0:00:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People like you will do no good
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you get out into society!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Class A, all right. \NWhat could have happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:49.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Tamura, stand up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me. Maybe Omichi has snapped again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay standing until you remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.11,0:00:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and say something, already!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.07,0:00:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi-{\i1}sensei{\i0}, is it possible that\Nyou have the wrong class schedule?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.78,0:01:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.78,0:01:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before you blame us, please check\Nyour notes once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.83,0:01:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.08,0:01:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I see. Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.30,0:01:15.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Tamura, sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.97,0:01:20.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, okay then.\NWell, let's resume our lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.51,0:01:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see, where was I?\NThe senate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.23,0:01:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the senate was the highest\Nlegislative and advisory body...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.86,0:01:35.32,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I scowled at the wind blowing\Nat my window of boredom{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.32,0:01:43.33,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so I could turn away\Nthe awkwardness I was feeling{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.62,0:01:51.54,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.54,0:01:56.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I nod noncommittally at today\Nas I hold it in my hand{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:02:02.35,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}projecting myself a little exaggeratedly{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:07.85,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I get the feeling that\Nsomething is about to change{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.85,0:02:12.94,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's all because of you\Ncalling out to my heart{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.32,0:02:19.74,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Peeking up at cloudy skies,\NI sense what's coming{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.74,0:02:27.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's reach out our hands\Nwith courage stronger than ever{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.21,0:02:32.79,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Light and shadow are both still far off{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.79,0:02:38.92,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but even so, we want to know\Nthe reason for this kindness{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.05,0:02:46.47,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go look now, beyond the brilliance\Nthat goes by nobody's name{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.47,0:02:54.52,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}before it all becomes a thing of the past{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:04.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Committing a Cardinal Sin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.28,0:03:01.41,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Earth Science Prep Room
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.41,0:03:05.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you're the one who\Nsaid you were going to do it in the fist place, aren't you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:09.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, um, please calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.66,0:03:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you stay out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.75,0:03:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you did have a reason, but what's\Nthe big idea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.63,0:03:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only natural that you'd at least call me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,would you care for a cookie?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would have been fine if you'd cancelled, if you\Nwould've only called!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.47,0:03:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}do{\i0} have a cell phone, right?!\NWhat were you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.47,0:03:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, well, I'll go buy some milk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.13,0:03:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}do{\i0} have a cell phone, right?! \NWhat were you thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.01,0:03:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it only concerned me, that'd be one\Nthing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.01,0:03:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you pulling that face?!\NListen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.72,0:03:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.85,0:03:29.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what trouble you're in?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.72,0:03:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daring move, there, Chitanda Eru.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just apologizing to me won't get you off the hook!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.52,0:03:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're usually so on the ball,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.56,0:03:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but when it comes to the basics,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.56,0:03:35.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll accomplish nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.98,0:03:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could stand to be a little more nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.69,0:03:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew what would happen,\Nbut you didn't do anything, did you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.28,0:03:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterward, it started raining,\Nthe wind started blowing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.49,0:03:45.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was lightning, and then finally,\Nit even started to hail!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.16,0:03:48.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet you wouldn't have noticed,\Neven if we {\i1}did {\i0}meet up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.04,0:03:50.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I did pick out\Nmy clothes, at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but before I knew it, they were\Nin shreds! In shreds!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.67,0:03:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And all of it is your fault, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}!\NAren't you worn out yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.71,0:03:57.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:03:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a breather.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.55,0:04:08.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't do it to save {\i1}you{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.39,0:04:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I have to say, you do get mad a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.43,0:04:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It relieves stress, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.48,0:04:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, if you had your\Nhead screwed on right,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be building up so\Nmuch stress before getting mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.77,0:04:21.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, you should take a\Npage from Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.86,0:04:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen her get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.86,0:04:26.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Speaking of not getting angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.41,0:04:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen {\i1}you {\i0}get angry,\Neither, Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0},
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor have I seen Oreki-{\i1}san {\i0}get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fuku-{\i1}chan {\i0}gets mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.83,0:04:36.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Satoshi gets mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.96,0:04:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.75,0:04:44.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sure. I don't get as\Nhopping mad as Mayaka does,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.84,0:04:45.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but sometimes, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.26,0:04:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even imagine you ever\Ngetting angry, Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.93,0:04:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I {\i1}am {\i0}human, after all. I {\i1}do {\i0}get mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.23,0:04:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't say.\NYou just don't make a big show\Nof venting your feelings at everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.23,0:05:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not very scary when he's angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not? Aw, don't think\Nmuch of me, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That does make me\Na little curious, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.61,0:05:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.41,0:05:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing that before too long,\NChitanda might hatch a scheme,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.66,0:05:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just to get Satoshi angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.50,0:05:16.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}, do you get angry, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.83,0:05:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ha, there's no way Oreki gets mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.55,0:05:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's so mild-mannered?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.34,0:05:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-mm. Because as a person, he's too\Nempty to even properly get mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.30,0:05:31.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. I don't care who you are,\Nthat's over the line, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.51,0:05:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, look, I got mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.81,0:05:36.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro's emotional shortcomings aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.39,0:05:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the way Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}doesn't get\Nangry is in a league of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.52,0:05:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call it tolerance, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.02,0:05:46.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, I wish you could be\Nmore laid-back, like Chitanda is.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.24,0:05:50.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an easy thing to ask, but it's\Nnot something I can do, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.12,0:05:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could never emulate Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.16,0:05:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I shouldn't take that\Nas a compliment, should I?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.41,0:05:57.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I had to say one way\Nor the other, it was one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.41,0:06:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just an evaluation; it's not\Na judgment, good or bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.38,0:06:03.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, now, leaving not {\i1}being\N{\i0}able to get angry aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.34,0:06:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,not getting angry is itself a virtue.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, wrath is a serious sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.59,0:06:11.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, I wish you'd go\Na little gentler on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.60,0:06:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sin?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.51,0:06:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the seven deadly sins, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.52,0:06:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. Way to go, Chitanda-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're generally known, so Mayaka,\Nyou've heard of them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.44,0:06:23.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Even I know about those.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.27,0:06:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought there were 108 sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the earthly desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.49,0:06:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Zat so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.91,0:06:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there's wrath, pride, gluttony, greed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.28,0:06:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.45,0:06:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Envy, lust, and sloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.04,0:06:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.21,0:06:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sloth, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.71,0:06:41.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is she looking at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.63,0:06:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, that\Nmakes you perfect, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.71,0:06:44.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.59,0:06:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're earnest, and you don't eat much.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.22,0:06:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you're too greedy,\Nand you're so diligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.97,0:06:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.68,0:06:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention, that is...\Nnot being slutty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.64,0:06:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.64,0:06:57.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way for us\Nto know if she's envious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.23,0:07:02.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These two are way beyond complimenting her;\Nnow they're just full-blown teasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.40,0:07:03.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's stop talking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:07.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, when I'm hungry, I eat plenty.\NShe doesn't seem like the envious type.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.90,0:07:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She seems like she could\Nbe Saint Eru, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.28,0:07:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Chitanda Eru" sounds like it could\Nbe an angel's name, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As in, "Uriel," "Gabriel,"\N"Chitanda-el (Eru)"?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.91,0:07:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop, I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.13,0:07:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:26.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, she scolded us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.96,0:07:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.96,0:07:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not talking to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}, Chi-{\i1}chan {\i0}is\Nmad now because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.55,0:07:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayaka, you were in on it too, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.31,0:07:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that not getting\Nangry is a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.35,0:07:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, that goes for the\Nother cardinal sins, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.78,0:07:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that pride and greed\Nare important things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.32,0:07:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In what way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think of someone\Nwho has no pride at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.49,0:07:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's someone who has no\Nself-confidence, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.49,0:08:00.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone doesn't have any greed,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it must make it hard for him\Nto support a family, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.29,0:08:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If people the world over\Nweren't envious of anyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.50,0:08:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there would never be any new\Ntechnologies developed, would there?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.72,0:08:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, um... I don't think you need\Nto listen so attentively to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.18,0:08:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, I get it. An interesting take.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:23.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, it's a matter of degree?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.69,0:08:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't think we should accept\Nthe term "deadly sin" as-is,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.27,0:08:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then apply it directly\Nto everything in our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.61,0:08:35.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you don't think\Nit's a bad thing to get mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:39.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct. If you couldn't\Nget angry at anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.20,0:08:41.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you probably couldn't grow to\Nlike anything, either, could you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.08,0:08:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can get angry. Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.08,0:08:48.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what you think,\Nthen why don't you ever get mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.63,0:08:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because it's exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.30,0:08:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't want to do anything exhausting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.73,0:09:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ch-Chitanda-{\i1}san {\i0}has been tainted\Nby Hotaro! How could this happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have spooks roaming around\NKamiyama High School!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spooks that are energy conservationists!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, snap out of it! Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}!\NThat's right, get it all out, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.95,0:09:17.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.07,0:09:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.03,0:09:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.79,0:09:26.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Joking, huh? And here I thought\NI'd found a kindred spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.37,0:09:29.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon. It was just\Nthe spur of the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.55,0:09:35.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as though I don't\Nget angry. Even {\i1}I {\i0}get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.26,0:09:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes indeed, such as...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.35,0:09:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When food gets wasted, I get angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.14,0:09:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A grain of rice is equal\Nto a drop of sweat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.19,0:09:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the daughter of a farmer,\Nall right. Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.94,0:09:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of getting angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:09:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't that you that got mad during\N5th period, in Omichi's class?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.45,0:10:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could I have forgotten?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.79,0:10:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would love to ask you about\Nthis matter, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw, crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious. I am curious.\NI am curious. I am curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.38,0:10:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious. I am curious.\NI am curious. I am curious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.27,0:10:27.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, guess I'll be off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.40,0:10:33.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, I would love to ask you\Nabout this matter, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.78,0:10:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.36,0:10:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. As it happens, during\Nmy 5th period math class,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:45.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.41,0:10:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you got mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't know what it was that\Noccurred that incurred my anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.59,0:10:58.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I didn't have to become angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.01,0:11:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but something occurred\Nwhich incurred my anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.47,0:11:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,only I don't know what\Nit was that occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.23,0:11:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said, something occurred\Nwhich incurred my anger...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.52,0:11:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyhow, now I am curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.03,0:11:21.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shousho {\i0}('The Warming')\NThe time ere the arrival of summer's heat
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:21.03,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.57,0:11:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight! Fight! Fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.16,0:11:26.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My 5th period today was math class.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.08,0:11:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi-{\i1}sensei {\i0}is the teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:35.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I believe that you both know pretty well\Nwhat he's like, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0} and Fukube-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.25,0:11:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should start explaining what\Nhappened from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.05,0:11:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei arrived at the classroom right about\Nthe same time the chimes sounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:48.22,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before entering the\Nroom, he stopped for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:50.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looked up at the class plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.77,0:11:53.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's something he has\Noften done before, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.61,0:11:58.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The first thing Sensei did was write\Na quadratic equation on the board...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:12:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Yes, the equation was a simple one,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he included bounds to the value of x.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.91,0:12:09.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He then called on Kawasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.87,0:12:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Come up and find the range of y."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.38,0:12:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}was clearly perplexed.\NOf course he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:22.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had not yet been taught\Nanything about ranges.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.22,0:12:26.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kawasaki-{\i1}san {\i0}answered with\N"I don't know how."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.76,0:12:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that moment, Sensei got mad,\Nand started to lay into us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.02,0:12:35.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next, he called on Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nwho is very good at math.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.77,0:12:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, he was unable to answer, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.48,0:12:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was at this moment\Nthat I finally realized
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that Sensei had made a mistake\Nwith regard to his lesson plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.74,0:12:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The other students realized it too,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.37,0:12:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the classroom became\Na little bit noisy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.08,0:12:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei became even more annoyed,\Nand started raking us over the coals.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.21,0:12:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and as if to punctuate his words,\Nhe beat the chalkboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.63,0:13:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There may have been some in the class\Nwho could have solved the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.55,0:13:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but everyone just looked at their desks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.30,0:13:10.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei finally called on Tamura-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nmade him stand up,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:12.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and started berating him again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.23,0:13:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I decided to stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.98,0:13:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked Sensei to once again check\Nour progress in his lesson plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:24.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's when I became angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.16,0:13:27.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what happened then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.99,0:13:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Sensei turned the\Npage of the textbook,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.33,0:13:35.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,whispered "Oh, right,"\Nand offered a word of apology,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.08,0:13:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,told Tamura-{\i1}san {\i0}to sit down again,\Nand continued teaching like normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.59,0:13:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's the kind of\Nteacher Omichi is, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.75,0:13:45.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Absolutely. I mean, thanks to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.26,0:13:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't tell you how much grief\NI went through after midterms.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.26,0:13:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We had teachers like him in elementary\Nand middle school, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.89,0:13:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's not especially a bad teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.31,0:13:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, your failing grade\Nis hardly Omichi's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.19,0:13:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better buckle down on the final.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.52,0:14:02.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened. What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.94,0:14:08.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was there anything about it\Nthat was that strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.24,0:14:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! What I wanted to ask you was how\Ndid Sensei make that kind of error?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.88,0:14:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei doesn't make too many mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.59,0:14:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you know. Omichi may\Nbe strict with his students,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.22,0:14:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he's also strict with himself, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, how did he make such a mistake?\NThat's what I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.14,0:14:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.27,0:14:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.06,0:14:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me. If you want to know\Nwhy Omichi made a mistake,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.94,0:14:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,go and peek around inside his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.15,0:14:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could just peek around,\Nthere'd be no challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:48.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? That's a shame.\NWell then, give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.78,0:14:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm too curious! Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0},\Nplease think about this with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.66,0:14:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.45,0:14:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you will just think about it\Nfor me, we can figure it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.04,0:14:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.04,0:15:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't talk to me like you're trying\Nto get a child to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.63,0:15:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, putting your hopes\Nin him is a shaky proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.55,0:15:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The guy was a katydid in a previous life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.51,0:15:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! Mayaka-{\i1}san{\i0}, you can tell past lives?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Nice going, Ibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.05,0:15:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, I'm more\Ncurious about our Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.81,0:15:17.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tch! What a headache.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.68,0:15:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am curious!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.44,0:15:27.15,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,The Calamity in Summer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei makes sure to write a note\Nin his textbook after class.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.66,0:15:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think that is for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.87,0:15:37.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he can check to see how far\Nhe has gotten in the lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.70,0:15:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I think. In addition,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.87,0:15:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he looks at the plate before going\Nin the classroom to double-check.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.88,0:15:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be easy to say\Nit's a perfect system,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so where is there any room\Nfor him to make a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.30,0:15:55.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His notes are probably something like,\Non page 15, he'll write "Class A, July 1."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.76,0:15:59.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, he'd lose track\Nof how far he has gotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.81,0:16:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could he have gotten the day wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, he would have gone backward;\Nhe wouldn't have gone ahead, would he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.77,0:16:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Use your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.44,0:16:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, she's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.82,0:16:13.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's bothering me.\NCan I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.16,0:16:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.82,0:16:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand you\Ngetting mad during this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:22.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just can't see you deciding to say\Nanything back to a teacher like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.21,0:16:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did get angry,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:30.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't think I was angry because\Nhe was saying mean things to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.30,0:16:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, was it because those who could\Nsolve the problem said nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.26,0:16:38.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Nobody would have wanted to go\Nup and solve it in that situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.85,0:16:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it because nobody else spoke up\Nto tell him he was mistaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.65,0:16:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it because you felt sorry for Tamura?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did feel bad for him, but I don't\Nthink I would get angry because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.95,0:16:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, it's natural for a student\Nwho doesn't remember
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.62,0:17:04.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the material from the previous class\Nto get yelled at, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.54,0:17:07.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when you ask me why I got angry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.84,0:17:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can be hard understanding\Nourselves, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.80,0:17:15.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What makes Chitanda angry,\Nand what makes her happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.10,0:17:24.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still don't know her well\Nenough to be able to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.52,0:17:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.48,0:17:33.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The part about Omichi writing a note\Nabout the class's progress in his book
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.32,0:17:37.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is probably right on the money.\NAnd yet, he still made a mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since they're moving forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.99,0:17:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there would have to be notes on the\Npages that came before the right one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.79,0:17:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that your class hadn't\Nyet learned about ranges, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.84,0:17:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.71,0:17:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Supposing you already had\Nlearned about them, then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.63,0:17:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.72,0:18:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi teaches math every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.68,0:18:04.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Class 1-A last year learned this, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.48,0:18:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're saying he mistook\Nthem for the year before,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.06,0:18:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid that couldn't happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.98,0:18:11.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.40,0:18:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,New teacher's edition textbooks\Nare re-issued every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.61,0:18:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever there are slight\Ncorrections made,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.40,0:18:19.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be inconvenient to have\Nthe two versions be different, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.57,0:18:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, the version that Omichi\Nis using is this year's 4th Edition.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.91,0:18:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure do have lots of\Nuseless knowledge, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.79,0:18:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a database, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.38,0:18:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm... Suppose Omichi does have\Na habit of writing things down,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and just got them mixed up? But then,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.64,0:18:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt that would convince Chitanda.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.48,0:18:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to admit, I don't quite get ranges.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.19,0:18:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a chore just for me to\Nwrite x and y in the same plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.36,0:18:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Omichi sets his sights on me,\NI'll be in for some real terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.11,0:18:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.11,0:19:00.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Class D already on the ranges unit?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.03,0:19:05.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.87,0:19:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Satoshi's class is already\Non the ranges unit,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.29,0:19:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but me and Chitanda's classes aren't yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So {\i1}that's {\i0}it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.42,0:19:19.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the look of someone\Nwho's thought of something.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.34,0:19:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chitanda...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.85,0:19:25.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure that there was\Na note on the page
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.22,0:19:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after where you had\Nactually reached, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.60,0:19:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right. I believe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was one he had written this year...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A note showing how far\Nthe class had gotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.11,0:19:37.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.15,0:19:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what if we were to assume\Nthat it wasn't for your class?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.74,0:19:46.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if it were a progress\Nmarker for Satoshi's class?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.29,0:19:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.37,0:19:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi is in charge of\Nfour classes... A, B, C, and D.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.00,0:19:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it wasn't for Class A or B,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.46,0:20:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that doesn't necessarily mean\Nit was for Class D, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.63,0:20:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what if it was for Class D, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.26,0:20:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it was Class D, it wouldn't surprise\Nme if he mistook it for Class A.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.68,0:20:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he could have\Nmistaken a C for an A, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.40,0:20:16.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Now you're not making sense again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.65,0:20:18.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't mistake an A for a D, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.90,0:20:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Omichi is a math teacher, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.07,0:20:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.95,0:20:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As a math teacher, there's a higher probability\Nthat he would mistake an A for a D.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.99,0:20:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's say that\NOmichi wrote on page 10, "July 1, A,"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.50,0:20:52.31,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,â™ªSketched by Oreki Hotaro
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.29,0:20:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then on page\N15, it would be "July 1, D," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.30,0:20:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what are you getting at here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.51,0:20:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no\Nway to mistake those two, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.63,0:20:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if he {\i1}did {\i0}mistake the A for a D,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.22,0:20:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,an incident like today's might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.72,0:20:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but how could it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.31,0:20:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because as a math teacher,\Nhe would write it like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.23,0:21:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! A lower-case "a" and "d"!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.99,0:21:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.95,0:21:08.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mm-hm, that's possible.\NOnce on an English test,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.66,0:21:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I lost points because they\Ncouldn't tell my letters apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you, too? Though in my case,\Nit was "n" and "h."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.50,0:21:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. That does seem possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.21,0:21:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whew, that's settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.63,0:21:29.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An "a" and a "d"... I can't\Nblame him for mixing those up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.64,0:21:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I really may have been\Na bit out of line with Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.39,0:21:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've gone and done a bad thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.36,0:21:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?! How do you figure that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.90,0:21:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Omichi was in the wrong, so you\Ncouldn't have been out of line!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.45,0:21:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Chi-{\i1}chan{\i0}, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.53,0:21:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, look how late it's gotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:50.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't about time we were leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.49,0:21:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? But, Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.24,0:21:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter, does it, Mayaka?\NThe mystery has been solved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean! Fuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.38,0:22:04.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The slow-to-wrath Chitanda became angry,\Nand wanted to know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.26,0:22:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Despite saying that getting angry\Nwasn't a bad thing, the truth is,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.97,0:22:13.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she never does want to get mad, does she?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.14,0:22:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hotaro and Chitanda-san, let's go!\NSo could the reason why Chitanda\Nwanted to know {\i1}why {\i0}she got mad
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.98,0:22:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. I'm straightening up now. \Nhave been because she wanted to give Omichi his due,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.65,0:22:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to believe that getting\Nmad was her own fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.11,0:22:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could that be the kind of\Nperson Chitanda Eru is?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.37,0:22:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.33,0:22:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I even know about Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.50,0:22:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I were able to predict\NChitanda's behavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.58,0:22:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if I thought I could read what's\Ninside her mind, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.46,0:22:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's {\i1}that{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.38,0:22:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Committing a cardinal sin. It's pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.14,0:22:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Refrain from such, refrain from such.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.31,0:22:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, how many times today have\NI been taken aback by Chitanda?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.56,0:22:59.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.94,0:23:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going home?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.94,0:23:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.78,0:23:07.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.74,0:23:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much. You are\Nalways helping me out, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.37,0:23:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a real hassle for me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.63,0:23:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you two waiting for?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.79,0:23:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going home?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.05,0:23:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, we'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.47,0:23:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we be going?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.01,0:23:31.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.68,0:23:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I'll pick it up again tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.14,0:23:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oreki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's probably true for you, Mayaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.11,0:23:46.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But think about it a minute...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.07,0:23:53.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, once again, a day of my\Nhigh school life is squandered.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.95,0:23:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deadly sin of sloth that I commit\Nis more than enough for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:04.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:08.71,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.71,0:24:12.72,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.72,0:24:17.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.19,0:24:38.20,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The heat of your budding warmth troubles me{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.04,0:24:48.96,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't you understand how I feel yet?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.46,0:24:55.97,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There isn't supposed to be\Nany significance in your glance{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.97,0:25:01.27,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I mean, it's the same one\Nyou give all your friends{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.27,0:25:07.06,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The tiny wishing star fading\Ninto the morning light{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.06,0:25:11.99,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the magic it works during the night\N(I wish you would notice){\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.99,0:25:15.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tonight it turns to love{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.11,0:25:18.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Meet me in a pleasant dream{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.83,0:25:22.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Make sure that you find me, okay?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.75,0:25:28.04,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our snooze-time date{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.30,0:25:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, "Upon Seeing the True Nature."
